\n\nIn [[North America]], only the 4.2 V8, 5.2 V10, and 6.0 W12 petrol engines are available. The 4.0 TDI was discontinued when the 4.2 TDI was introduced.{{clear}}\n\n== {{anchor|D4|4H|third}} Third generation (D4, ''Typ'' 4H; 2011\u20132017) ==\nThe third generation of the Audi A8 was introduced in Miami on 30 November 2009. The chassis was built on the [[Volkswagen Group D platform#D4|Volkswagen D4 platform]].\n\n=== Initial release ===\n{{Infobox automobile\n| name = Third generation (D4/4H)\n| image = 2012 Audi A8 (4H) 4.2 quattro sedan (2018-10-12) 01.jpg\n| production = 2010\u20132017\n| model_years = 2011\u20132017\n| assembly = Germany: [[Neckarsulm]]<br>Russia: [[Kaluga]] ([[Volkswagen|Volkswagen Group Rus]]) (2013\u20132016)\n| designer = Christian Winkelmann (2007)\n| platform = [[Volkswagen Group MLB platform|Volkswagen MLB]]\n| engine = {{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = Inline-four petrol engine\n|1 = 2.0 [[Inline 4 engine|I4]] [[Turbocharger|T]][[Fuel Stratified Injection|FSI]]\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = V6 petrol engine\n|1 = 2.5 [[V6 engine|V6]] FSI (China)\n|2 = 3.0 [[V6 engine|V6]] TFSI\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = V8 petrol engine\n|1 = 4.0 V8 TFSI\n|2 = [[4.2 FSI|4.2]] [[V8 engine|V8]] [[Fuel Stratified Injection|FSI]]\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = W12 engine\n|1 = 6.3 [[W12 engine|W12]] FSI\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = V6 diesel engine\n|1 = 3.0 [[V6 engine|V6]] [[Turbocharged Direct Injection|TDI]]\n}}\n{{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = V8 diesel engine\n|1 = 4.2 V8 TDI\n}}\n| transmission = {{collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0;| title = Automatic transmission\n|1 = 8-speed [[ZF 8HP transmission|ZF 8HP]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.insideline.com/straightline/2010/02/audi-considering-8-speed-transmissions-for-majority-of-its-lineup.html|title=Audi Considering 8-Speed Transmissions for Majority of Its Lineup|accessdate=17 February 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100217232241/http://blogs.insideline.com/straightline/2010/02/audi-considering-8-speed-transmissions-for-majority-of-its-lineup.html| archivedate= 17 February 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[tiptronic]] [[automatic transmission|automatic]]\n}}\n| wheelbase = {{convert|2992|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br>{{convert|3122|mm|1|abbr=on}} (LWB)\n| length = {{convert|5131|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br>{{convert|5267|mm|1|abbr=on}} (LWB)\n| width = {{convert|1948|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n| height = {{convert|1461|mm|1|abbr=on}}<br>{{convert|1471|mm|1|abbr=on}} (LWB)\n| weight = {{convert|1977|kg|1|abbr=on}} A8L 3.0TL<br>{{convert|2000|kg|1|abbr=on}} A8 4.2L<br>{{convert|2020|kg|1|abbr=on}} A8 L 4.2L<br>{{convert|2165|kg|1|abbr=on}} A8 L 6.3L\n| sp = uk\n}}\n{{Multiple image | align = left | direction = vertical | width =\n| image1 = 2012 Audi A8 (4H) 4.2 quattro sedan (2018-10-12) 02.jpg\n| caption1 = Audi A8 (pre-facelift)\n| image2 = Audi-A8-Japan.JPG\n| caption2 = Interior (pre-facelift)\n}}\n\n==== New features ====\nChanges include:<ref name=\"audi-mediaservices.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2010/02/01/the_new_audi_a8__.html |title= The new Audi A8 \u2013 The sportiest sedan in the luxury class |accessdate= 2014-12-30 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20141231011547/https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2010/02/01/the_new_audi_a8__.html |archivedate= 2014-12-31 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n* Full [[LED headlamp]]s with [[Automatic high beam]] switching or Audi [[adaptive light]] ([[Xenon]]) with [[variable headlight range control]].\n* Enhanced MMI [[Multi Media Interface]] with [[touchpad]] & [[handwriting recognition]] for the phone and navigation system, using [[Nvidia]] [[Tegra]] [[system on a chip]] for very high processing speed.\n* Optional 1,400&nbsp;watt [[Bang & Olufsen]] sound system.\n* [[Driver assistance system]]s networked using [[FlexRay]] technology.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.insideline.com/audi/a8/2011/2011-audi-a8-4-2-fsi-first-drive.html |title= 2011 Audi A8 4.2 FSI First Drive |accessdate= 16 February 2010 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100211135914/http://www.insideline.com/audi/a8/2011/2011-audi-a8-4-2-fsi-first-drive.html |archivedate= 11 February 2010 |url-status= live }}</ref>\n* [[Hard disk drive]] GPS navigation with [[3D computer graphics]] with [[Google Earth]].<ref>{{cite news |last= White |first= Joseph B. |title= Virtual Dashboards: The Next Must-Have? |newspaper=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |page= B11 |date= 20 January 2010 }}</ref>\n* Navigation system coordinates input to the adaptive headlights, transmission, [[adaptive cruise control]] and [[electronic stability control]].<ref name=\"audi-mediaservices.com\"/>\n* [[Passive infrared sensor|Infrared]] [[Night Vision Assistant]] with [[pedestrian]] recognition.<ref name=\"audi-mediaservices.com\"/>\n* [[Broadband internet]] with [[3G|UMTS 3G]] and [[WLAN-Hotspot]].\n* First production Audi with a [[Collision avoidance system]]: [[Pre sense]]<ref name=\"audi-mediaservices.com\"/> (similar to [[Mercedes-Benz]] [[Pre-Safe]]). The full version of the system (Pre Sense Plus) works in four phases. In the first phase, the system provides warning of an impending accident, while the hazard warning lights are activated, the side windows and sunroof are closed and the front seat belts are tensioned. In the second phase, the warning is followed by light braking, strong enough to win the driver's attention. The third phase initiates autonomous partial braking at a rate of 3&nbsp;m/s\u00b2 (9.8&nbsp;ft/s\u00b2). The fourth phase decelerates the car at 5&nbsp;m/s\u00b2 (16.4&nbsp;ft/s\u00b2) followed by automatic deceleration at full braking power, roughly half a second before projected impact. A second system, called (Pre Sense Rear), is designed to reduce the consequences of [[rear-end collision]]s. The sunroof and windows are closed and seat belts are prepared for impact. The optional memory seats are moved forward to protect the car's occupants. The system uses [[sensor fusion]] with twin [[radar]] and a mono camera.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bosch-presse.de/TBWebDB/en-US/PressText.cfm?id=4570 |title=Extensive safety in the new Audi A8. Bosch predictive emergency braking system goes into series production |accessdate=2 June 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100921045137/http://www.bosch-presse.de/TBWebDB/en-US/PressText.cfm?id=4570 |archivedate=21 September 2010 }}</ref> and was introduced in 2010.\n\n==== A8 (L) (2010\u2013) ====\nThe third-generation Audi A8 (L) ('''''Typ'' 4H''') is based on the [[Volkswagen Group MLB platform]], but retains the Audi Space Frame aluminium construction of the previous A8, making it the lightest all-wheel drive car in the full-size luxury segment, while also giving it best-in-class fuel economy.<ref>{{cite web |last= Peterson |first= Thane |url= http://www.businessweek.com/lifestyle/content/oct2010/bw2010104_140585.htm |title= Review: 2011 Audi A8 |work=[[Business Week]] |date= 2010-10-05 |accessdate= 2011-02-02 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110119123104/http://www.businessweek.com/lifestyle/content/oct2010/bw2010104_140585.htm |archivedate= 2011-01-19 |df= dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.windingroad.com/articles/reviews/comparison-2012-bmw-750li-xdrive-vs-2012-audi-a8l-42/ |title=Winding Road - Comparison Test: 2012 BMW 750Li xDrive vs. 2012 Audi A8L 4.2 |website= windingroad.com |accessdate=14 July 2015 }}</ref> The quattro all-wheel drive system splits torque with a default bias of 40 percent front and 60 percent rear.\n\nThe vehicle was unveiled at Design Miami 2009 on 30 November 2009,<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.audiusanews.com/newsrelease.do?id=1601 |title=Audi Media Site : Home : Home |work=Audiusanews.com |date=2009-11-27 |accessdate=2010-10-03| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20101025201325/http://audiusanews.com/newsrelease.do?id=1601| archivedate= 25 October 2010 | url-status= live |df= dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"audi-a8-2010\">{{cite web|url=https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2009/11/27/world_premiere_of.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html|title=World premiere of new Audi A8 in Miami|date=2009-11-27|publisher=[[Audi AG]] |df= dmy-all }}</ref> followed by the [[North American International Auto Show#2010|2010 North American International Auto Show]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2010/1/b0010284.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2010/1/b0010284+/car/A20060003+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1a2010\u5e95\u7279\u5f8b\u8eca\u5c55\u5831\u5c0e\uff1a2011\u5e74\u53f0\u7063\u767c\u8868\uff0c\u5927\u6539\u6b3eAUDI A8\u6b63\u5f0f\u9996\u6f14|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nEarly models include A8 [[4.2 FSI]] quattro (372PS), A8 3.0 TDI quattro (250PS), A8 4.2 TDI quattro (350PS).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2009/12/01/the_new_audi_a8__.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html|title=The new Audi A8 \u2013 The sportiest sedan in the luxury class|work=Audi MediaCenter|accessdate=14 July 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525080749/https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2009/12/01/the_new_audi_a8__.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html|archivedate=25 May 2013}}</ref> A8 3.0 TDI (204PS) was added later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2010/02/01/the_new_audi_a8__.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html|title=The new Audi A8 \u2013 The sportiest sedan in the luxury class|work=Audi MediaCenter|accessdate=14 July 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525082241/https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2010/02/01/the_new_audi_a8__.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html|archivedate=25 May 2013}}</ref>\n\nInitial internal combustion engine options comprise 4.2-litre [[gasoline direct injection|Fuel Stratified Injection]] (FSI) petrol and [[Turbocharged Direct Injection]] (TDI) diesel V8s, with {{convert|273|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|258|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} respectively. A 3.0-litre V6 TDI with either {{convert|184|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} or {{convert|150|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} will be available later. A 6.3-litre [[W12 engine]] only for the long wheelbase model was made available in 2010, and compared to its predecessor it has a larger displacement and direct fuel injection.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.girlracer.co.uk/motoring/road-tests/4815-audi-a8-first-drive.html|title=Audi A8 first drive|accessdate=9 June 2010}}</ref> All engines are mated to the new eight-speed [[ZF 8HP transmission|ZF 8HP]] automatic transmission. Although other Audi vehicles such as the 2010 [[Audi S4]] and 2011 [[Audi A7]] had switched from the 4.2 L V8 to the 3.0 L supercharged V6, the Audi A8 retained a higher-output 4.2 L V8 as the base engine for the 2011 and 2012 model years in North America.\n\nTaiwan models went on sale on the 11th November 2010. Early models include 3.0 TFSI quattro (290PS).<ref name=\"\u805a\u7126\u9818\u8896\u4eba\u58eb\u773c\u5149\uff0cAUDI\u65b0A8\u9802\u7d1a\u65d7\u8266412\u842c\u8d77\u98a8\u96f2\u767b\u5834\">{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2010/11/b0110315.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2010/11/b0110315+/car/A20060002+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1a\u805a\u7126\u9818\u8896\u4eba\u58eb\u773c\u5149\uff0cAUDI\u65b0A8\u9802\u7d1a\u65d7\u8266412\u842c\u8d77\u98a8\u96f2\u767b\u5834|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== A8 L (2010\u20132017) ====\nThe vehicle was unveiled at Auto China 2010,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2010/4/b0040394.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2010/4/b0040394+/car/A20060003+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1a2010\u5317\u4eac\u8eca\u5c55\u6436\u5148\u5831\uff1a\u5927\u6539\u6b3eAUDI A8 L\u9996\u6f14\uff0c\u6700\u5feb\u5e74\u5e95\u5728\u53f0\u4e0a\u5e02|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2010/4/b0040517.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2010/4/b0040517+/car/A20060003+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1a2010\u5317\u4eac\u8eca\u5c55\u5831\u5c0e\uff1aAUDI A8L\u6539\u6b3e\u5168\u7403\u9996\u6f14\uff0c\u6700\u5feb\u5e74\u5e95\u53f0\u7063\u4e5f\u770b\u5f97\u5230\uff01|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref> followed by the 2011 Taipei Motor Show (A8 L W12 quattro).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2011/12/b1120318.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2011/12/b1120318+/car/A20060001+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1a2012\u53f0\u5317\u8eca\u5c55AUDI\u6436\u5148\u5831\uff1a\u9577\u8ef8\u7d93\u6fdf\u65d7\u8266\uff0cA8L W12\u53f0\u7063\u8c6a\u6c23\u9996\u6f14|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nGerman models went on sale in the fall of 2010. Early models include a 3.0 TFSI quattro (290PS), a 4.2 FSI quattro (372PS), a W12 6.3 FSI quattro (500PS), a 3.0 TDI quattro (250PS) and a 4.2 TDI quattro (350PS).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2010/07/12/the_new_high-tech.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html|title=The new high-tech flagship of the brand \u2013 The Audi A8 L|work=Audi MediaCenter|accessdate=14 July 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525083848/https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2010/07/12/the_new_high-tech.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html|archivedate=25 May 2013}}</ref>\n\nTaiwan models went on sale on the 11th November 2010. Early models include a 3.0 TFSI quattro (290PS) and a 4.2 FSI quattro (372PS).<ref name=\"\u805a\u7126\u9818\u8896\u4eba\u58eb\u773c\u5149\uff0cAUDI\u65b0A8\u9802\u7d1a\u65d7\u8266412\u842c\u8d77\u98a8\u96f2\u767b\u5834\"/> The A8L W12 quattro was added in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2011/12/b1120549.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2011/12/b1120549+/car/A20060001+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1a\u56db\u74b0\u81f3\u5c0a\u964d\u81e8\u5bf6\u5cf6\uff0cAUDIA8L W12 quattro\u9802\u7d1a\u8c6a\u83ef\u79d1\u6280\u65d7\u8266\u5373\u5c07\u5728\u53f0\u4e0a\u5e02|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref> the A8L 4.0 TFSI quattro was added in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2012/12/b2120447.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2012/12/b2120447+/car/A20060001+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1a\u9802\u7d1a\u5962\u83ef\u65d7\u8266\u518d\u51fa\u64ca\uff0cAUDI A8L V8 4.0 TFSI quattro 599\u842c\u6975\u6548\u4e0a\u5e02|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nChinese models went on sale in 2011. Early models include an A8L 3.0 TFSI low quattro (289PS), and an A8L 3.0 TFSI high quattro (333PS).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2011/3/b1030027.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2011/3/b1030027+/car/A20060002+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1a\u7e3d\u66f8\u8a18\u6700\u611b\uff01AUDI A8L\u8c6a\u6c23\u9032\u8ecd\u4e2d\u570b\u9ad8\u7d1a\u8eca\u58c7\uff01|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== A8 hybrid concept (2010) ====\nThe concept vehicle includes a 2.0 TFSI engine rated at {{convert|211|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|350|Nm|2|abbr=on}} of torque at 1,500\u20134,200 rpm, a disc-shaped electric motor rated {{convert|45|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|211|Nm|2|abbr=on}} of torque, lithium-ion battery, luggage space of 400 liters (14.13 cubic feet), 21-inch wheels with 265/35 tires, Prism Silver body colour with Spectra Flair accent colour, 'hybrid' lettering on both front fender and illuminated doorsteps with 'hybrid' insignia.<ref>{{cite web|author= Jonathon Ramsey RSS feed |url=http://www.autoblog.com/2010/03/03/geneva-2010-audi-a8-hybrid/ |title=Geneva 2010: Audi A8 Hybrid a concept in name only |publisher=Autoblog.com |date= |accessdate=2012-04-08 |df= dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2010/03/02/the_efficiency_standard.html|title=The efficiency standard \u2013 the Audi A8 hybrid|work=Audi MediaCenter|accessdate=14 July 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140305193320/https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2010/03/02/the_efficiency_standard.html|archivedate=5 March 2014 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe vehicle was unveiled in 2010 at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2010|Geneva Motor Show]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2010/3/b0030043.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2010/3/b0030043+/car/A20060003+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1a2010\u65e5\u5167\u74e6\u8eca\u5c55\u5831\u5c0e\uff1aA8 Hybrid\u3001A1 e-tron\u6982\u5ff5\u73fe\u8eab\uff0cAUDI\u5c55\u793a\u74b0\u4fdd\u6c7a\u5fc3|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== A8 L long-term evolution broadband prototype (2011) ====\nIt is a version of the A8 L demonstrating [[4G]] [[LTE (telecommunication)|long-term evolution (LTE)]] broadband technology. Developed in collaboration with [[Alcatel-Lucent]], the car's [[mobile broadband]] connection is a fourth generation (\u20184G\u2019) technology with data transfer speeds of up to 100Mbit/s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.audi.co.uk/about-audi/latest-news/audi-a8-l-prototype-gets-state-of-the-art-broadband-connection.html |title=Audi A8 L Prototype gets state-of-the-art broadband connection |publisher=Audi.co.uk |date=2011-03-21 |accessdate=2012-04-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110831084928/http://www.audi.co.uk/about-audi/latest-news/audi-a8-l-prototype-gets-state-of-the-art-broadband-connection.html |archivedate=2011-08-31 |df= dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.worldcarfans.com/111021730755/audi-a8-prototype-gets-broadband-internet-capability |title=Audi A8 prototype gets broadband internet capability |publisher=Worldcarfans.com |date= |accessdate=2012-04-15 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nDuring the 2011 [[Consumer Electronics Show]] in Las Vegas, [[Rupert Stadler]], Chairman of the Board of Management of AUDI AG, announced that LTE technology would be used in cars by early 2011. The A8 L prototype was unveiled weeks later.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2011/02/16/audi_a8_with_broadband.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html |title= Audi A8 with broadband Internet connection |publisher= Audi-mediaservices.com |date= 2011-02-16 |accessdate= 2012-04-15 |df= dmy-all |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20130525081716/https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2011/02/16/audi_a8_with_broadband.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html |archive-date= 2013-05-25 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\n==== A8 L Security (2011\u2013present) ====\nThe A8 L Security is an armoured version of the A8 L with class VR 7 ballistic protection standard (tested as per BRV 2009 guidelines), resistance to explosions against a military hand grenade (tested as per ERV 2010 guidelines), with certain areas of the armouring complies with the criteria for class VR 9 and VR 10, a core safety cell made from hot-formed armoured steel, aramid fabric, ceramics, special alloyed aluminium and multilayer glass; overlapping protective materials at the joints, aluminum side sills with solid steel sections, aluminum alloy armored floor, side windows, windshield and rear window made of special glass with a polycarbonate coating; optional electromechanical window openers, closing assist feature comes standard for the doors, communication box in the luggage compartment (light ceramic doors, aluminum frame), optional battery and the fuel tank protection, two-way communication system with a speaker in the single-frame grille and microphones for the cabin and exterior, an emergency exit system with pyrotechnical separating screws in the hinges, fire extinguisher system, emergency fresh-air system with two oxygen cartridges, a smoke extractor for the passenger compartment, an LED signaling system for convoy travel, flashing lights, a siren, a preparation for professional mobile radio systems, a flag holder, a permanently installed telephone, an accident data recorder, an additional rearview camera and a heated windshield plus partially heated side windows, four-zone climate control system with an ionizer to freshen the air, electric rear blinds, the sonorous Bose surround sound system and a TV tuner, rear are two individual seats with power adjustment, front comfort seats with heating and optional massage and ventilation functions, standard full-leather package, optional relaxation seat (adjustable right-hand rear seat with a power-adjustable footrest, heating and massage), optional center console with large storage compartments and rear seat entertainment system with two 10.2-inch displays, optional folding table, optional refrigerator optional parking heater, Bluetooth car phone online, integrated UMTS module, optional separate telephone handsets, 19-inch forged wheels featuring in semipolished two-tone finish, 255/720 tires with a high load index of 117, synthetic rings on the rims, optional full-size spare tire.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.audisite.com/1769/high-security-audi-a8-planned-for-high-contingency/ |title= High-Security Audi A8 planned for High Contingency |work=AudiSite.com |date= 2011-02-16 |accessdate= 2011-02-21 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe first model includes a W12 engine rated at {{convert|500|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on|order=flip}} and {{convert|625|Nm|0|abbr=on}} of torque. Deliveries began in late summer 2011. An additional engine model with improved fuel efficiency went on sale in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|author= Jeff Glucker RSS feed |url=http://www.autoblog.com/2011/02/16/audi-a8-l-security-blends-serious-protection-with-luxury-and-sty/ |title=Audi A8 L Security blends serious protection with luxury and style |publisher=Autoblog.com |date=2011-02-16 |accessdate=2012-04-08 |df= dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.audi.ca/ca/brand/en/tools/news/pool/2011/2/high-security_version.html|title=Audi Canada|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.audizine.com/news/news.php?nid=183|title=Audizine: News: High-security version of the Audi A8 soon to be launched|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe vehicle was unveiled at the [[Geneva Motor Show#2011|2011 Geneva Motor Show]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://blog.caranddriver.com/audis-a8l-security-so-bombproof-it-can-even-survive-the-phaeton/|title=Audi\u2019s A8L Security So Bombproof, It Can Even Survive the Phaeton|work=Car and Driver |date=2011-02-18 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nDeliveries began in late summer 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2011/2/b1020280.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2011/2/b1020280+/car/A20060002+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1a\u9802\u7d1a\u623f\u8eca\u518d\u9032\u5316\uff0cA8 L Security\u79d1\u6280\u884c\u52d5\u5821\u58d8\uff01|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== A8 hybrid (2012\u2013present) ====\n{{multiple image | direction = vertical | width = 220\n|image1=Audi A8 2.0 T Hybrid (6147658222).jpg |caption1=2011 Audi A8 Hybrid\n|image2=Audi A8 L W12 quattro tiptronic Phantomschwarz Heck.JPG |caption2=Audi A8 L (Europe; pre-facelift)\n|image3=Audi S8 (D4, Facelift) \u2013 Frontansicht, 16. August 2014, Essen.jpg |caption3=Audi S8 (facelift)\n|image4 = Audi S8 (D4, Facelift) \u2013 Heckansicht, 16. August 2014, Essen.jpg|caption4 = Audi S8 (facelift)\n}}\n\nThe production version includes an electric motor rated at {{convert|54|PS|kW hp|0|abbr=on|order=flip}} and {{convert|210|Nm|0|abbr=on}} of torque, 1.25 [[kWh]] lithium-ion battery, 18-inch 10-spoke alloy wheels in turbine blades design (optional 19-inch), hybrid badges, metallic paint finish (optional Arctic Silver body colour), three-zone automatic air conditioning, LED headlights, and a BOSE sound system. Pure electric mode is available for either a top speed of {{convert|100|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}} or for up to {{convert|3|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} at a constant speed of {{convert|60|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}}. It went on sale in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|author= Sebastian Blanco RSS feed |url= http://www.autoblog.com/2011/08/24/audi-spills-the-beans-on-production-37-mpg-a8-hybrid/ |title=Audi spills the beans on production 37 mpg A8 Hybrid |publisher=Autoblog.com |date= |accessdate=2012-04-08 |df= dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.audi.de/de/brand/de/neuwagen/a8/a8/pakete.html#page=/de/brand/de/neuwagen/a8/a8/motor/hybrid.html&layer=/de/brand/de/neuwagen/a8/a8/motor/hybrid.engine_compare.4hc0fw_0.techdata.html|title=Pakete > A8 > Audi Deutschland |publisher= |accessdate= 14 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2011/08/24/consistently_efficient.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html|title=Consistently efficient \u2013 the Audi A8 hybrid|work=Audi MediaCenter|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe vehicle was unveiled at the [[Frankfurt Motor Show#2011|2011 Frankfurt Motor Show]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2011/8/b1080587.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2011/8/b1080587+/car/A20060001+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title= 2011\u6cd5\u862d\u514b\u798f\u8eca\u5c55\u6436\u5148\u5831\uff1aAUDI A8 Hybrid\u91cf\u7522\u73fe\u8eab\uff0c\u5e74\u5e95\u9032\u8ecdHybrid\u5e02\u5834 |work=AutoNet|date=2011-08-25 |df= dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2011/9/b1090230.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2011/9/b1090230+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title= 2011\u6cd5\u862d\u514b\u798f\u8eca\u5c55\u5831\u5c0e\uff1a\u608d\u52d5\u4e16\u754c\u7684\u74b0\u4fdd\u8c6a\u83ef\u65d7\u8266\uff0cAUDI A8 Hybrid\u5168\u7403\u9996\u6f14 |work=AutoNet|date=2011-09-15 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==== A8 L W12 Audi exclusive concept ====\nIt is a limited (50 units) version of the A8 L W12 with seats upholstered in Cognac-colored leather by [[Poltrona Frau]], inlays made from the wood olive ash natural, light gray-brown veneer, sill trims with \"Audi exclusive concept\" lettering, deep-pile carpeting.\n\nThe vehicle was unveiled at the 2011 [[Frankfurt Motor Show]].<ref>{{cite web |author= Drew Phillips |url= http://www.autoblog.com/2011/09/15/audi-a8-w12-exclusive-concept-frankfurt-2011/ |title= Audi adds more luxury to the A8L W12 with the Exclusive Concept |publisher= Autoblog.com |date= 2011-09-15 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==== A8 L hybrid ====\nThe long wheelbase version of the A8 hybrid was unveiled in 2010 at the [[Beijing Auto Show]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/bizchina/2010autochina/2010-04/30/content_9797560_2.htm|title=Car stars shine at Auto China 2010|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== {{anchor|D4S8}} S8 4.0 TFSI quattro (2012\u20132015) ====\nThe D4 series Audi S8 4.0 TFSI quattro went on sale in 2012. The D4 S8 was based on the A8 platform, considered in America to be the \"short wheel base\" comparative to the A8L. Like the previous iteration, the D4 S8 costs less than the A8 L W12.<ref name=\"insideline1\">{{cite web|last=Jacquot |first=Josh |url=http://www.insideline.com/audi/s8/2013/2013-audi-s8-first-drive.html |title=2013 Audi S8 First Drive |publisher=Insideline.com |date=2011-10-26 |accessdate=2012-05-25 |df= dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"fourtitude1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fourtitude.com/news/publish/Features/article_7313.shtml |title=Driven: 2012 Audi S8 |publisher=Fourtitude.com |date=2011-11-16 |accessdate=2012-05-25 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe S8 can accelerate from {{convert|0|to|100|km/h|mph|0|abbr=on}} in 4.2 seconds. It is powered by a [[4.0 TFSI|4.0-litre]] [[gasoline direct injection|TFSI]] [[twin-turbo|biturbo]] V8 engine with {{convert|382|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}}. The engine utilises cylinder deactivation so it can run as a V4 for better fuel economy.<ref name=\"insideline1\"/> The S8's engine is shared with the [[Bentley Continental GT#Second generation (2012\u2013present)|Bentley Continental GT]], while a detuned variant of the engine makes 420&nbsp;hp which is found in the 2013 [[Audi S6]], [[Audi S7]], and Audi A8. Direct competitors include the BMW [[Alpina#Alpina B7|Alpina B7]] and Mercedes-Benz S63 AMG, which also have biturbo V8 engines.<ref name=\"roadandtrack1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.roadandtrack.com/tests/drives/2012-audi-s8 |title=2012 Audi S8 \u2013 2012 Audi S8 First Drive Review on |publisher=Roadandtrack.com |date=2011-09-07 |accessdate=2012-05-25 |df= dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"lpauto1\">{{cite web |url=http://newcars.lpauto.ca/NewVehicles/en/2013/Audi/A8/4.0T+Premium+4dr+All-wheel+Drive+quattro+Sedan/CAC30AUC042B0 |title=New 2013 Audi A8 4.0T Premium 4dr All-wheel Drive quattro Sedan for sale in Richmond, British Columbia &#124; LP Auto |publisher=Newcars.lpauto.ca |date=2012-05-01 |accessdate=2012-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130512214638/http://newcars.lpauto.ca/NewVehicles/en/2013/Audi/A8/4.0T+Premium+4dr+All-wheel+Drive+quattro+Sedan/CAC30AUC042B0 |archive-date=2013-05-12 |url-status=dead |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe vehicle was unveiled at the 2011 [[Frankfurt Auto show]], and went on sale in spring 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.audi-mediaservices.com/publish/ms/content/en/public/pressemitteilungen/2011/08/31/world_premiere_of.standard.gid-oeffentlichkeit.html|title=World Premiere of Audi S Models at the IAA 2011|work=Audi MediaCenter|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nTaiwan models went on sale in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2013/5/b3040668.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2013/5/b3040668+/car/A20060001+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|title=AutoNet \u6c7d\u8eca\u65e5\u5831\uff1aAUDI S Model\u9ad8\u6027\u80fd\u5bb6\u65cf\u65b0\u4f5c\uff0c S8\u9802\u7d1a\u6027\u80fd\u65d7\u8266\u623f\u8eca\u50b2\u8996\u964d\u81e8|publisher=|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe S8 ceased production in 2015, to be replaced by the S8 Plus for the latest iteration of this generation before the facelift in 2018.\n\n=====S8 Plus 4.0 TFSI Quattro (2016\u20132018)=====\nBased on the same chassis and underpinnings as the D4 S8, the D4 S8 Plus became the sole option for ordering the S8-variant of the Audi A8 line, in the 2016 and 2017 model years. The S8 Plus was dialed up to {{Convert|605|hp|kW|abbr=on}} out of the same powerplant as the previous S8, by remapping the turbo boost and fuel delivery of the engine. Additionally, the Carbon Ceramic braking system is standard on the S8 Plus. The vast majority of options on the S8 Plus were identical to the previous S8; however, had darkened tail lights standard, and the option for adding carbon fiber styling elements such as the mirror caps, rear lip spoiler, rear diffuser, and front lip. With a high-optioned build, the S8 Plus would outprice the A8 W12; which terminated in 2016.\n\n==== Engines ====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible\" style=\"font-size:98%;\"\n|+Petrol engines\n!Model!!Years!!Type!!Power at rpm!!Torque at rpm!!Acceleration 0\u2013{{convert|100|km/h|0|abbr=on}}(sec